      "writtenOn": "2020-11-10T23:34:26Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is all tangential.\n\nI\u0027m kind of interested to see if in follow ups it makes sense to get rid of this field entirely.\n\nI think it\u0027s our solution to not immediately resizing down doing something like\n\n    SkTArray foo;\n    foo.reserve_back(lots);\n    foo.push_back(...);\n    // At this point foo.count() is 1, likely well enough less than `lots` that we\u0027d shrink,\n    // not seeing the future push_back() calls about to come.\n    foo.push_back(...);\n    ...\n\nbut I kind of think you don\u0027t need to track that bit if you just make growing ops only check to grow up,\nshrinking ops only check to shrink down.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 470,
        "startChar": 7,
        "endLine": 470,
        "endChar": 26
      },
